name: StreamedResponse
comment: An HTTP response where the response body is received asynchronously after the headers have been received.

stream.name: stream
stream.comment: The stream from which the response body data can be read. This should always be a single-subscription stream.

contentLength.name: contentLength
contentLength.comment: The size of the response body, in bytes. If the size of the request is not known in advance, this is -1.

persistentConnection.name: persistentConnection
persistentConnection.comment: Whether the server requested that a persistent connection be maintained.

reasonPhrase.name: reasonPhrase
reasonPhrase.comment: The reason phrase associated with the status code.

constructors.comment: Creates a new streaming response. http/http.StreamedResponse.StreamedResponse-.stream should be a single-subscription stream.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides http/http.StreamedResponse.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and http/http.StreamedResponse.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the http/http.StreamedResponse.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
http/http.StreamedResponse.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to http/http.StreamedResponse.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If http/http.StreamedResponse.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of http/http.StreamedResponse.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.
